get_metric(25.10)                                            get_metric(25.10)

Name get_metric - Gets the current state of metric(s)
Syntax
Parameters  -help  Outputs  a brief description that includes type and default
       information for each get_metric parameter. For a  detailed  description
       of  the  command  and  all  of its parameters, use the man command: man
       get_metric -branch <list_of_patterns> Specifies  list  of  patterns  to
       match  snapshot  branches. This will limit all output to metrics stored
       in snapshots whose branch matches the specified branch.  This  requires
       any  inheritance  to  be  re-run  to exclude inherited values from non-
       matching  snapshots.  Data_type:  string,  optional  -exclude_inherited
       Specifies  not to return any inherited value. Data_type: bool, optional
       -id <id_name> Specifies the database ID to output. Default  is  current
       database.  Data_type: string, optional -names <label_name> List of pat-
       terns to match snapshot names Name of label to get metrics from  (wild-
       cards  supported); no label reports current metrics. Data_type: string,
       optional <pattern_name> Specifies the list of patterns  to  match  met-
       rics.  Supports  wildcard  *.  Use  of  *  gets all metrics. Data_type:
       string, optional -pending Returns metrics from  the  pending  (not  yet
       created)  snapshot. Data_type: bool, optional -pending_top Returns met-
       rics  from  the  entire  pending  (not  yet  created)  snapshot  stack.
       Data_type:  bool,  optional  -raw Returns metrics as raw value (without
       normalization to defined units). Data_type: bool, optional
